---
import '../styles/global.css'
import '@fontsource/barlow/300.css'
import '@fontsource/barlow/700.css';
import hmw from '../images/intervention-finder/fi-hmw.png';
import ideation from '../images/intervention-finder/fi-ideation.png';
import home from '../images/intervention-finder/fi-home.png';
import prisonerSearch from '../images/intervention-finder/fi-prisoner-search.png';
import results from '../images/intervention-finder/fi-results-cropped.png';
import programmeDetail from '../images/intervention-finder/fi-programme-detail.png';
import axCover from '../images/home/ax-cover.png';
import adReport from '../images/home/ad-report.png';

---

<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
		<meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
		<title>Simon Castillo - Finding rehabilitative programmes</title>
	</head>
	<body>
        <main>
            <header>
                <nav class="top-nav">
                    <a href="/" class="home-link">Simon Castillo</a>
                </nav>
            </header>
            
            <div class="case-study-hero">
                <h1 class="primary-color heading-l">Finding rehabilitative programmes</h1>
                <ul class="inline-list aligned-center">
                    <li>Ministry of Justice</li>
                    <li>My role: Interaction Designer</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <section class="centred-partial-width">
                <div class="quick-summary">
                    <h2 class="heading-s primary-color section-heading">Quick summary</h2>

                    <p>The challenge here was to help probation practitioners find the right rehabilitation courses or activities for a person in prison. For example, to address specific issues like substance abuse or managing relationships.
                    </p>

                    <p>I worked with a service designer to lead our team through a short design sprint and launch the project.
                    </p>
                </div>			
			</section>
            <section class="centred-partial-width">
                <h2 class="heading-m primary-color section-heading">Setting the project up for success</h2>
                <p>The sprint included a review of discovery research, sessions defining scope, and ideation sessions. This helped to define the key problems for the project:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>deciding which accredited programmes are suitable for a specific person's needs</li>
                    <li>checking that the person's schedule in prison aligns with the programme's dates</li>
                    <li>automating this process versus letting probation practitioners use their expert judgement</li>
                </ul>
            </section>
            <div class="img-section">
                <figure class="img-container">
                    <img src={hmw.src} alt="A digital whiteboard showing various opportunities for the project on post-its. They are grouped into themes." class="border-radius-s">
                    <figcaption class="body-xs caption-partial-width">Prioritising opportunities in the form of 'How might we' statements.</figcaption>
                </figure>
            </div>
            <div class="img-section">
                <figure class="img-container">
                    <img src={ideation.src} alt="A digital whiteboard with sketches and mock-ups of different people's ideas. There are also post-its describing each idea." class="border-radius-s">
                    <figcaption class="body-xs caption-partial-width">Leading a remote ideation session.</figcaption>
                </figure>
            </div>
            <section class="centred-partial-width">
                <h2 class="heading-m primary-color section-heading">High-fidelity prototyping and user research</h2>
                <p>Taking the best ideas from the sprint, I built a prototype in Figma, which we tested with 7 probation practitioners and took through one round of iteration.</p>
            </section>
            <div class="two-column img-section">
                <figure class="img-container">
                    <img src={home.src} alt="A mock-up of a landing page for the 'Search for an intervention' service." class="border-radius-s">
                    <figcaption class="body-xs">A high-fidelity design of the landing page for the service.</figcaption>
                </figure>
                <figure class="img-container">
                    <img src={prisonerSearch.src} alt="A mock-up of a page for searching for a specific prisoner by their number or personal details." class="border-radius-s">
                    <figcaption class="body-xs">Pulling in a prisoner's data automatically and comparing the details of their needs to what programmes offer.</figcaption>
                </figure>
            </div>
            <div class="two-column img-section">
                <figure class="img-container">
                    <img src={results.src} alt="A search results page with a list of programmes and an open filter menu. " class="border-radius-s">
                    <figcaption class="body-xs">Search results automatically matched to the person's needs and ordered by relevance.</figcaption>
                </figure>
                <figure class="img-container">
                    <img src={programmeDetail.src} alt="A page showing the details of a specific programme. It includes an overview, description and locations." class="border-radius-s">
                    <figcaption class="body-xs">Programme details with concise descriptions, nearby locations and links to start referring the person.</figcaption>
                </figure>
            </div>
            <section class="centred-partial-width">
                <aside>
                    <blockquote>
                        <p>
                            "I’m smiling because it looks like you’re giving me exactly what I want… We need this to do our job better." &mdash; Prison Offender Manager 
                        </p>
                    </blockquote>
                </aside>
                <h2 class="heading-m primary-color section-heading">Next steps</h2>
                <p>The prototype received positive feedback from all user research participants, with relatively small tweaks for the next version.</p>
                <p>I moved to another project soon afterwards, but this was a good example of using a short design sprint to take a team quickly from discovery to initial solution.</p>
            </section>
            <section class="centred-partial-width padding-bottom-four">
                <div class="quick-summary">
                    <h2 class="heading-s primary-color section-heading">View more of my work</h2>
                    <div class="quick-summary-body border-bottom">
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="heading-m primary-color">Accurx</h3>
                            <ul class="no-bullets">
                                <li><a href="/accurx">Collaborative workspaces</a></li>                            
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <img src={axCover.src} alt="Two Accurx screens overlapping. One is a workspace list page and the other shows an inbox." class="border-radius-s">
                    </div>
                    <div class="quick-summary-body padding-top-two">
                        <div>
                            <h3 class="heading-m primary-color">Ministry of Justice</h3>
                            <ul class="no-bullets">
                                <li><a href="/disclosure-checker">When to disclose your criminal record</a>
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <img src={adReport.src} alt="Two Accurx screens overlapping. One is a workspace list page and the other shows an inbox." class="border-radius-s">
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
        </main>
        <footer class="aligned-center footer">
			<h2 class="primary-color heading-m">Get in contact
            </h2>
            <p class="centered-partial-width">Feel free to get in touch with any queries:
            </p>
			<ul class="inline-list">
				<li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/castillosimon/" target="_blank">LinkedIn</a></li>
				<li><a href="mailto:simcast8@gmail.com" target="_blank">Email</a></li>
			</ul>
		</footer>

    </body>
</html>